<div type="apparatus"><head>Apparatus</head><p>l. 1, this line must describe the objects which are not to be disposed of, i.e. the tomb and all its appertinances including probably <foreign lang="grc">τὴν ἐπικε<supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied>μένη<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied> <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">σορὸν</supplied></foreign>. Final letters, only the  uprights visible.</p><p>l. 6, the final <foreign lang="grc">Σ</foreign> is uncertainly read.</p></div><div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>[...] no-one is to dispose of the tomb and its burial places and the sarcophagus lying (on it),  either by surrendering it or by legal conveyance or in any other way; but in the sarcophagus there shall be placed only  Publius Aelius Claudius Smaragdos Julianos and Publius Aelius Attalos his father, and if anyone should dare to bury anyone else in it, he will be (treated as) sacrilegious and accursed and will pay a penalty to the most sacred treasury of 15,000 silver denarii, as laid down by Smaragdos and [...]</p></div>

